        </question>
    </easy>
    <medium>
        <question>
            <text>An ideal gas expands isothermally from V to 2V. Work done?</text>
            <option id="A">nRT ln(2)</option><option id="B">nRT</option><option id="C">nRT log(10) 2</option><option id="D">Zero</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>W = nRT ln(V2/V1).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Carnot engine absorbs 1000J heat from source at 500K and rejects heat to sink at 300K. Work done?</text>
            <option id="A">400 J</option><option id="B">600 J</option><option id="C">200 J</option><option id="D">800 J</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>eta = 1 - 300/500 = 0.4. W = eta * 1000 = 400J.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>A gas is compressed adiabatically to half its volume. Relation between T1 and T2? (gamma=1.5)</text>
            <option id="A">T2 = T1 * sqrt(2)</option><option id="B">T2 = 2 T1</option><option id="C">T2 = T1 / 2</option><option id="D">T2 = T1 * 4</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>TV^(gamma-1) = const. T1 V^0.5 = T2 (V/2)^0.5. T2 = T1 * (2)^0.5.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Work done in adiabatic expansion is given by:</text>
            <option id="A">nR(T1 - T2) / (gamma - 1)</option><option id="B">nR(T1 - T2)</option><option id="C">nR(T2 - T1) / gamma</option><option id="D">Zero</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Standard formula.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>For a reversible process, cyclic integral of dQ/T is:</text>
            <option id="A">Zero</option><option id="B">Positive</option><option id="C">Negative</option><option id="D">Infinite</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Clausius inequality equality.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Ideal gas eq for adiabatic process in terms of P and T?</text>
            <option id="A">P^(1-gamma) T^gamma = C</option><option id="B">P T^gamma = C</option><option id="C">P^gamma T = C</option><option id="D">P T = C</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>V = T/P. P(T/P)^gamma = P^(1-gamma)T^gamma = const.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Efficiency of Otto cycle depends on:</text>
            <option id="A">Compression ratio</option><option id="B">Temperature limits only</option><option id="C">Pressure</option><option id="D">Fuel</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>eta = 1 - 1/r^(gamma-1).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Refrigerator COP is 5. Heat extracted 1000J. Work input?</text>
            <option id="A">200 J</option><option id="B">5000 J</option><option id="C">100 J</option><option id="D">500 J</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>COP = Q2/W. 5 = 1000/W. W=200.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>When a system is taken from state i to f along path 1, Q=50, W=20. Path 2 Q=36. W=?</text>
            <option id="A">6</option><option id="B">14</option><option id="C">30</option><option id="D">10</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>dU = Q-W = 50-20=30. Path 2: 30 = 36 - W. W=6.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Temperature of source is increased. Efficiency of Carnot engine:</text>
            <option id="A">Increases</option><option id="B">Decreases</option><option id="C">Same</option><option id="D">Zero</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>eta = 1 - T2/T1. Inc T1, ratio decreases, eta increases.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Two isotherms intersect:</text>
            <option id="A">Never</option><option id="B">At T=0</option><option id="C">At 2 points</option><option id="D">Always</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Temp cannot be two values at same state.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Gas expands according to PV^2=C. Work done V1 to V2?</text>
            <option id="A">Polytropic formula</option><option id="B">Isothermal formula</option><option id="C">Adiabatic</option><option id="D">Zero</option>
