        <question>
            <text>Efficiency of engine is 1/6. Reduce sink temp by 62C, efficiency doubles. Source Temp?</text>
            <option id="A">372 K</option><option id="B">273 K</option><option id="C">400 K</option><option id="D">100 K</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>1 - T2/T1 = 1/6 => T2/T1 = 5/6. T2 = 5/6 T1. New: 1 - (T2-62)/T1 = 2/6 = 1/3. (T2-62)/T1 = 2/3. 5/6 T1 - 62 = 2/3 T1. (5/6 - 4/6)T1 = 62. 1/6 T1 = 62. T1 = 372 K.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Heat pump COP relation with Engine efficiency?</text>
            <option id="A">COP = 1/eta</option><option id="B">COP = 1 - eta</option><option id="C">COP = 1 + eta</option><option id="D">None</option>
